The paper focuses on feature engineering from relational databases, which is a common task in data science and machine learning. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a deep neural network approach, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity of finding optimal features, which relates to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
